article.description: High Point comes back to beat Liberty 67-60
article.headline: High Point comes back to beat Liberty 67-60
article.linkText: High Point comes back to beat Liberty 67-60
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- John Brown scored 16 points and had 10 rebounds in High Point's 67-60 win over Liberty on Wednesday. It was High Point's third win in a row -- played in five days -- and Liberty's seventh consecutive loss. Devante Wallace had 12 points for High Point (13-13, 9-4 Big South) and Anthony Lindauer 11. Liberty (9-19, 3-10) was led by Antwan Burrus with 15. High Point trailed 30-26 at halftime after Liberty's Tomasz Gielo capped the first-half scoring with a 3-pointer. At the 8-minute mark of the second half, High Point was behind 49-44 before going on a 15-0 run -- highlighted by six Brown points -- for a 10-point lead with 2:57 left. Davon Marshall scored the next six Liberty points to get within 61-55, but High Point made 6 of 8 free throws in the final 2 minutes.
